<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Endures Heat Wave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria is enduring a rare heat
wave, with temperatures reaching 40 degrees centigrade in some
areas including the capital and other big cities, meteorological
departments said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The temperature in Sofia reached 35.2 degrees centigrade on
Tuesday, breaking the city's previous record of 35 degrees
98 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Plovdiv, the country's second largest city, endured a
temperature of 38 degrees on Tuesday, while southern cities
Svilengrad and Sandanski reached 39 degrees and 40 degrees
respectively the same day.
</P>
<P>
The heat is unbearable for many people, especially the old and
children, and hospitals are overcrowded with patients suffering
from heatstroke.
</P>
<P>
The heat also caused many fires and traffic accidents around
the country.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasts say the heat will last through August.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
