<HEADLINE> 27 Injured in Greek Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A road collision in Greece's
seaside resort of Voula, more than 100 kilometers north of Athens,
on Wednesday injured 27 people, including eight seriously.
</P>
<P>
An Athens urban transport bus collided with a truck which
ignored a red light and went into the lane of oncoming traffic,
both drivers were seriously injured, police said.
</P>
<P>
Last weekend, nearly 30 people were killed and some 300 injured
in 276 traffic accidents throughout Greece.
</P>
<P>
In Greece, road accidents kill about 2,500 people and injure
30,000 each year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
