<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Govt Awards Honorary Certificates to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABAB, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian health minister
Adem Ibrahim awarded on Wednesday honorary certificates to the 13
members of the ninth Chinese medical team to the country.
</P>
<P>
The certificate signed by minister Adem says that, on behalf
of the government of the Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia,
thank the Chinese members for having "made contributions to
rendering medical and health services for Ethiopian people".
</P>
<P>
The certificate praises the Chinese doctors for their
"remarkable successes in carrying out humanitarian project in the
field of medicine for improving health care in Ethiopia and
developing the friendly relations between the peoples of two
countries".
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony held at the ministry, minister Adem and
Chinese medical team leader Cao Xiaoyan highly praised the
friendly cooperation between China and Ethiopia and expressed
their determination to further develop the friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
The ninth Chinese medical team assigned by Henan province,
came to work at Adama hospital, Ethiopia, in August 1996 and has
successfully ended their two-year services. They will leave for
China soon.
</P>
<P>
The ninth Chinese medical team was granted "the model of
Chinese medical teams" by Chinese health ministry in March, 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
