<HEADLINE> Egypt Calls for Halting Kosovo Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Egypt on Wednesday appealed to the
international community for help to put an end to the continued
Serbian security force operations against ethnic Albanians in
central Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"Egypt is totally convinced of the importance of putting an end
to the operations against innocent civilians living in Kosovo," a
Foreign Ministry spokesman said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Albanians are fleeing their homes in Kosovo as
Serbian forces and the Kosovo Liberation Army fight for control of
the Yugoslav province where ethnic Albanians make up 90 percent of
the population.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman urged all institutions defending human rights to
shoulder their responsibility in a bid to stem bloodshed and
prevent further deterioration of the situation in the entire
region.
</P>
<P>
"Appealing to the concerned parties for an immediate halt of
acts of violence, Egypt urged for the return of the Albanian
refugees to their homeland in order to reach a just settlement
rapidly through dialog, serious comprehension of co-existence and
tolerance," he said.
</P>
<P>
Egypt is currently following up with deep concern the latest
developments taking place in Kosovo, he said.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 people have been killed and 300 missing since the
crisis in Kosovo began in February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
