<HEADLINE> Landslide Kills 40, Injures Over 20 in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A landslide has killed 40
people and injured over 20 in Fefa Sheba district, Oromiya
Region, over 300 kms southwest of the Ethiopian capital.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency Wednesday quoted local officials as
saying that 20 of the deceased were women and only 11 bodies were
recovered and buried.
</P>
<P>
According to the officials, 1,332 people have been displaced
and 157 houses destroyed by the landslide on Monday.
</P>
<P>
About 215 domestic animals were killed and crops destroyed,
they added.
</P>
<P>
A team dispatched by the district council have been helping
residents set up temporary shelters and provide food and medical
treatment to the victims, according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
