<HEADLINE> 165 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A total of 165 members of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed in the
southeastern Turkey since July 31, the Anatolia News Agency said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted officials with the Emergency Rule Region
Office as saying that the PKK members were wiped out in the
military operations by government troops in Diyarbakir and other
southeastern provinces.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, five PKK members were captured and two others
surrendered.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a guerilla war against the
government since 1984 to establish an independent Kurdish state
in southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
More than 35,000 people have been killed in the armed
conflicts between the PKK militants and government troops. 
</P>
</TEXT>
