<HEADLINE> Annan Expresses Grave Concern over Recent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fighting between the rebels and the forces of the Government broke
out on Tuesday in a few towns of the country. The Congolese
Government accused Rwanda of being the ally of the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Congolese Foreign Minister Bizima Karaha vowed on Wednesday to
topple President Laurent Kabila after joining up with army rebels
in the east.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Annan said the recent developments in the
country threaten the stability of the region and further
compromise its reconstruction and development.
</P>
<P>
Annan reaffirmed the need to respect the sovereignty and
territorial integrity of the country, and called on regional
leaders to do their utmost to prevent the crisis from widening
and to promote a peaceful settlement.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief appealed to all concerned in the country to
refrain from acts of persecution, harassment or discrimination
against any segment of the population, and to respect the human
rights of all.
</P>
<P>
Annan said he remained available to contribution to the
restoration of peace and stability in the region in any way it is
deemed useful.  
</P>
</TEXT>
