<HEADLINE> First UAE Emergency Aid Airlifted to Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The first plane carrying
humanitarian emergency supplies to Sudan left here Wednesday for
the Sudanese capital of Khartoum.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to Xinhua, Nasser Hamadi, information official of the
Red Crescent Society of the United Arab Emirates (UAE), said that
this package was part of the humanitarian assistance to be
extended to the hunger and drought-stricken people in Sudan.
</P>
<P>
He added that the flight was carrying 40 tonnes of foodstuffs
out of a total of 160 tonnes to be airlifted aboard five flights
to Sudan in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
The relief supplies have been prepared by the Zayed Foundation
for welfare and humanitarian works in Abu Dhabi in cooperation
with the UAE Red Crescent Society. 
</P>
