<HEADLINE> Mahathir: Malaysia to Continue Raising Funds Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said Thursday Malaysia will push ahead with
efforts to raise funds abroad to revive its economy.
</P>
<P>
But the means by which the government would do this would not
be made public to prevent "rogue currency speculators" from
derailing such efforts, he said at a gathering in Ipoh, northern
state of Perak, some 205 kilometers from here, according to
Malaysia's national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
"We will find other means (to raise funds) but we cannot reveal
them because then the rogue currency speculators will find ways to
derail our efforts," he was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the government had to borrow from foreign sources
and not from the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to enable the
two agencies recently set up by the government to purchase
non-performing loans and recapitalize local companies.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the latest tactics to undermine Malaysia's
economy became apparent when two days before Deputy Prime Minister
Anwar Ibrahim was scheduled to leave for an overseas trip to
explain the country's economy and raise foreign funds, the rogue
currency speculators downgraded Malaysia's credit rating through
two international credit rating agencies, Moody's and Standard &AMP;
Poor's.
</P>
<P>
He said after attacking the country's currency which had
dropped by over 60 percent and the stock market which plunged
across the board, these rogue speculators were now attacking
Malaysia's ability to raise funds abroad.
</P>
<P>
"They deliberately undermined our efforts to revive our own
economy," he said, adding their only intention was to destroy the
economy.
</P>
<P>
Anwar's proposed roadshow was to raise 2 billion ringgit (0.5
billion U.S. dollars) in the international capital market to be
used as funding for Pengurusan Danaharta Nasional Bhd, the asset
management company set up to buy over the non-performing loans of
the banking system.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said these speculators not only wanted to control the
economies of countries in Asia but also their politics and
determine who their leaders should be.
</P>
<P>
He said these speculators were not only greedy for money but
also for power to control the economy, politics and to control the
world.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said his main objective in meeting the people was to
explain to them the situation faced by the country to enable them
to understand the problem.
</P>
<P>
He said what was important was that the people did not create
chaos in the country and instead maintained their solidarity.
</P>
<P>
He reminded the people that if there was chaos, the government
would not be able to concentrate on reviving the economy.
</P>
<P>
"We need the concentration, we must face it and if there are
all sorts of things happening behind our backs, maybe we will not
be successful," he said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the people should understand the economic turmoil,
which could be considered extraordinary, because if they did not
comprehend it they would not be concerned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
