<HEADLINE> Top Legislator Stresses Need to Preserve Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, China's top legislator,
recently stressed the importance of pollution control and
environmental protection and the implementation of related laws
and regulations.
</P>
<P>
Li, Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), made the comments in a fact-finding trip to Dalian
in northeast China's Liaoning Province between August 4-6.
</P>
<P>
Li was on his fifth visit to the city, one of China's six top
cleanest cities, and noted "great changes" in local environmental
protection projects and in the implementation of environmental
laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
He also visited the Xinghai Bay Business Zone and commended the
local government's efforts to transform the former saltern and
garbage dump into a picturesque complex with conference, business
and recreation facilities.
</P>
<P>
Li exhibited special interest in pollution control at
coal-fired power plants. He visited the Huaneng Dalian Power Plant
and voiced approval for the facilities dust removal rate of 99
percent. He encouraged the plant's management to continue to
attach high importance environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a forum attended by local officials, legislators
and local residents, Li said that environmental protection is a
basic state policy which is directly related to China's long-range
development. He stressed that "pollution control and environmental
protection will promote both economic and social efficiency."
</P>
<P>
He pointed to Dalian's achievements as a clean city, but noted
that it has a long way to meet standards for one of the world's
cleanest cities. Li urged local authorities to continue
implementing the state policy on sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Li urged legislators and local residents to supervise the
enforcement of China's seven environmental protection laws.
</P>
<P>
Li also conducted a study on modifications to the Law on the
Organization of Village Committees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
