<HEADLINE> Djibouti to Consider More Incentives for Malaysian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Djibouti which already
offers tax-free investment returns for up to 10 years, is willing
to consider further incentives for Malaysian investors.
</P>
<P>
Djibouti is willing to discuss further the kind of incentives
needed by Malaysian investors, Djiboutian President Hassan Gouled
Aptidon told a press conference at the end of his six-day official
visit here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
