<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> D.R.Congo Faces Serious Rebellion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINSHASA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic Republic of Congo
(D.R.Congo) is facing a serious conflict after rebels elected a
political chief in Goma to coordinate the fight against the
government of Laurent-Desire Kabila.
</P>
<P>
Veteran political opposition leader Arthur Zahidi Ngoma was
elected Wednesday as the chief of the rebellion staged by Tutsi
Banyamulenge soldiers, who are Congolese originated from Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Born on September 18, 1947, in Kalima in the province of
Maniema, eastern Congo, Zahidi Ngoma is a native Congolese and was
an opponent of both former President Mobutu Sese Seko and
President Kabila.
</P>
<P>
A specialist in international law and educated at the Sorbonne
University, Paris, Ngoma had worked for the United Nations
Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) and
served briefly as prime minister under Mobutu.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the eastern Kivu region said that the situation
there was getting worse as rebel soldiers had taken control of the
city of Uvira in southern Kivu, after fierce fighting between the
rebels and soldiers loyal to the government Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The rebels, who declared their rebellion against the government
on Sunday, already have control of Goma and Bukavu, the two major
cities in the Kivu region.
</P>
<P>
Fighting was also reported in the northern city of Kisangani and
the extreme western city of Kitona, where a big military base is
located.
</P>
<P>
The government Wednesday again condemned Rwanda for backing
the rebellion and threatened to "export war to Rwanda".
</P>
<P>
Kinshasa also called on the international community to treat
Rwanda as "a criminal state" which it said should not be allowed
to take advantage of the sympathy from the world for the 1994
genocide suffered by the country.
</P>
<P>
While denying involvement in the war, Rwandan President Pasteur
Bizimungu said that "if there is serious reason to be involved,
Rwanda will jump into the dancing pool".
</P>
<P>
The rebellion started after President Kabila ordered all
military personnel of Rwanda to leave the country.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda was believed to have played a big role in helping Kabila
come to power 15 months ago.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Kivu region is a hotbed for the growth of renegades
engaging different governments in the region, including those of
Rwanda, Burundi and Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
