<HEADLINE> UK Government Urges Nationals to Leave Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The British Foreign Office on
Thursday urged its nationals in the Democratic Republic of Congo
to leave as armed conflict between the rebels and government
forces spread.
</P>
<P>
"In view of the uncertainty and the risk of serious escalation
in the fighting, we strongly advise against traveling to the
Democratic Republic of Congo and advise British nationals ... to
leave while commercial flights are still operating," the Foreign
Office said.
</P>
<P>
Reports say the Tutsi-led uprising against President Laurent
Kabila has spread to the west of the Democratic Congo with
fighting in an oil town and a naval base.
</P>
<P>
There are around 400 British nationals registered with the
British embassy in Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Office also urged the African country and its
neighbors to cooperate in efforts to deal with any threat to
regional stability. 
</P>
