<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Calls for Peaceful Solution to Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
Secretary-General of the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
Thursday calls on all parties involved in the crisis in the
Democratic Republic of Congo to "exercise restraint and seek a
peaceful solution."
</P>
<P>
According to an OAU press release faxed to Xinhua, Salim also
appealed to "countries of the region to help in promoting a
peaceful solution, which takes into account the need to respect
the sovereignty, unity and territorial integrity of the
Democratic Republic of Congo."
</P>
<P>
"I am saddened by the fact that these developments have
emerged so soon after the last crisis in that country and at a
time when efforts were being deployed to promote the building of
foundations for a stable and democratic Congo," Salim said.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief went on to call for the convergence of all
efforts to promote a speedy and peaceful solution to the present
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Salim said he is undertaking consultations with the leaders of
the region and will be dispatching a mission to Kinshasa to
consult with the authorities there as well as to the countries of
the region to see how best the OAU can make its contribution to
the search for a peaceful solution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
