<HEADLINE> Xie Jun to Meet Russian Galliamoa in 10-game Duel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Former world women's champion Xie
Jun of China will take on Russian A. Galliamoa in a scheduled
10-game duel on August 15 in north China's Shenyang to vie for the
right to challenge reigning world champion Zsuzsa Polgar of H
ungary.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the Chinese Chess Association (CCA), the Russian
Chess Federation (RCF) confirmed that Galliamoa will come to China
with coaches A. Kahlifman and A. Philippenko and officials M.
Myphtakhov and B. Khropov.
</P>
<P>
Under the competition format, the player who collected 5.5
points will win the duel and automatically become the candidate to
challenge Polgar.
</P>
<P>
The players will get one point from a win and 0.5 point from a
draw in the 120,000 U.S. dollars duel.
</P>
<P>
If they were deadlocked at 5:5 after 10 games, the two sides
would meet in a 11th game. But if the 11th game still ended with
a tie, the outcome would be decided with a draw.
</P>
<P>
Xie Jun, who won the world champion in 1991, was dethroned by
Polgar after 13 games in Jaen, Spain, in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The duel was scheduled to last until August 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
