<HEADLINE> Typhoon Otto Threatens East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Typhoon Otto hit southern
sections of east China's Jiangxi Province early this morning
bringing timely heavy rainfall to the drought-stricken area of the
province.
</P>
<P>
However, the local flood control department predicted the
localized rain carried by Otto will threaten even more extensive
flooding in the northeastern part of the province.
</P>
<P>
The typhoon changed course and moved into Jiangxi from the
south depositing an average of 39.5 mm rainfall in the southern
areas in the grips of a month-long drought. 
</P>
