<HEADLINE> HK Official: Good Parents-Children Relations Help Deter Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Administrative Secretary Anson
Chan of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Thursday
called on parents and children to deter juvenile crime hand in
hand by communicating with and caring for each other.
</P>
<P>
During a visit to the Junior Police Call (JPC) Summer Camp at
Wu Kwai Sha Youth Village in Ma On Shan, Chan told JPC members
that many youngsters committed crime because of family problems
and poor relationship with their parents.
</P>
<P>
"You must realize that your family is your pillar of support.
When you come across problems, you should discuss them with your
parents and family members and seek their advice," she stressed.
</P>
<P>
She asked parents to help their children solve problems in a
caring and open attitude. Moreover, they should set an example for
their children to help them foster proper values of life and grow
up as good citizens, Chan said.
</P>
<P>
Running from August 4 to 7, this year's camp attracted more
than 1,500 JPC members. It has adopted the theme of this year's
Fight Crime Publicity Campaign "Your Children's Future Hangs on
Parental Care".
</P>
<P>
Since its inception in 1974, the JPC scheme has grown into the
largest youth organization in Hong Kong with nearly 210,000
youngsters on its membership roll.
</P>
<P>
Chan highly commended the JPC members for their contributions
in community services and for helping the police fight against
crime. 
</P>
