<HEADLINE> Fourth Yangtze Flood Peak Approaching Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The fourth Yangtze flood peak is
approaching Yichang in central China's Hubei Province, with water
level reaching 53.14 meters, and a flow rate of 57,200 cubic
meters per second at 2 p.m. today.
</P>
<P>
The water level at a section of 267 kilometers long in Yichang
has surpassed the danger mark, as a result of recent torrential
rainfall in Sichuan Province, Chongqing Municipality, and the
Three Gorges area in the upper reaches of Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
More than 30,000 people in the city have been organized to
guard the dyke around the clock.
</P>
<P>
The dyke of Bailizhou town, a small island and home to over
100,000 residents, was in danger yesterday. The situation is under
control today, according to local officials.  
</P>
