<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jobless Total Sees Modest Rise in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment in Germany registered a
modest rise of 59,400 to a total of 4,134,500 in July, about
220,000 less than in the same month of last year, the German
Federal Labour Office said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate rose to 10.7 percent from 10.5 percent in
June, less than the 11.4 percent for June last year, the latest
figures showed.
</P>
<P>
Klaus Leven, deputy president of the labor office, attributed
the increase in the June jobless total entirely to seasonal
factors, adding that the rise was significantly less than in the
previous years.
</P>
<P>
"The current economic upswing in Germany is giving a gradual
boost to the job market," Leven said.
</P>
<P>
German Labor Minister Norbert Bluem also saw in the June data
a confirmation of the government assessment that a trend of
reversal is setting in on the job market.
</P>
<P>
"We are making progress step by step in the battle against
unemployment," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
