<HEADLINE> Namibian Cabinet Okays SADC Mining Protocol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Namibian cabinet has
agreed to join a regional campaign to standardize working
conditions in mines and to reduce environmental hazard caused by
mining.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet Tuesday approved the ratification of the Southern
African Development Community (SADC) Protocol on Mining, which
was signed last year by regional heads of state in Blantyre,
Malawi, South African Press Association reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet mandated the Minister of Mines and Energy to make
preparations to table the protocol in parliament for
ratification.
</P>
<P>
Under the protocol, governments of the 14-nation bloc are
required to jointly develop and observe internationally accepted
standards of mining safety, miners' health and environmental
protection. 
</P>
