<HEADLINE> Mozambique Earns $28.5 Million from Transfer of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique has earned about 342
billion Meticais (28.5 million U.S. Dollars) from the transfer of
fixed assets including housing, commercial and industrial real
estate since the transfer process started in 1993.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Joaquim Mauricio, director of the Central
Commission of Fixed Assets Appraisal and Transfer of Mozambique,
at a meeting on the transfer of fixed assets held in the Maputo
suburbs Wednesday, the Noticias newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to Mauricio, 63 percent of the country's 56,770 real
estate has been applied for transfer, of which 54 percent has
been approved.
</P>
<P>
Twenty percent of the income from the transfer of fixed assets
are to be handed over to the coffer, 30 percent allocated for the
Housing Fund, and the rest goes to the original owner for refund.
</P>
<P>
Under the country's Fixed Assets Act, one (national citizen)
may pay cash or instalments while buying the house he or she is
residing. However, the installments should be in less than 25
years.
</P>
<P>
Mauricio said the government will simplify procedures to speed
up the process of real estate transfer.
</P>
<P>
Most of the existing state-owned fixed assets came from early
independence when state-ownership was initiated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
