<HEADLINE> Nigeria Expects New Cabinet Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A new cabinet is expected to
emerge in Nigeria, as the Provisional Ruling Council (PRC) and
the National Council of States (NCS) hold a joint meeting in
capital Abuja Thursday.
</P>
<P>
PRC is the now Nigeria's highest ruling body, comprising of
major military leaders, while the NCS is comprised of military
administrators of all states.
</P>
<P>
Media reports here said the meeting will also decide the
composition of a new independent electoral commission that will
monitor all elections under the new transition to civil rule
program.
</P>
<P>
General Abdulsalam Abubakar, assuming office on June 9
following the sudden death of late military leader General Sani
Abacha, sacked the cabinet he heritaged on July 8.
</P>
<P>
On July 20, he sacked all the political parties as well as the
national electoral commission on the basis that the transition
program under General Abacha has no credibility due to massive
rigging.
</P>
<P>
He, however, refused the opposition's demand for a government
of national unity, promising that new cabinet will be able to
reflect the interest of various groups.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar also announced a new transition program that will see
the military handing over to an elected civilian government on May
29, 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
