<HEADLINE> Shandong's Private Sector Surges Ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The private sector has grown
rapidly in east China's Shandong Province, one of the country's
major economic powerhouses.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the province approved 7.7
percent and 22 percent more individually run industrial and
commercial businesses and private enterprises. The growth rates
are the highest in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Shandong had a total of 2.46 million individually run
industrial and commercial businesses and 81,000 private firms by
the end of June, according to the latest official statistics.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, the individual businesses and private
enterprises had 6.43 million employees in aggregate, more than 12
percent of the provincial labor force.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's individual business and private firms reported a
combined 53.2 billion yuan in retail sales of consumer goods in
the first half of this year, about 53 percent of the provincial
total during the period. They also turned in 1.84 billion yuan in
taxes, about 11.9 percent of the local fiscal revenue, and
employed 75,000 laid-off workers.  
