<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Keen to Develop Environmental Protection Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province has
reported success in recent years in developing environmental
protection technologies.
</P>
<P>
The Jinan Yuxing Chemical Plant used to produce a large amount
of poisonous chromium dregs, which were the leading pollutants at
the source of the Xiaoqinghe river, a major river in the province.
</P>
<P>
Because of technical cooperation between the plant and Jinan
Iron and Steel Company, the pollution problem has been resolved,
saving the steel company annually up to one million yuan in raw
materials and the plant 1.7 million yuan in residue treatment
costs.
</P>
<P>
Shandong is an important industrial province where air blowers,
water pumps and boilers are the top three energy-consumption
equipment in large industrial projects, accounting for about
one-fourth of the province's use of electricity and one-third of
its coal consumption.
</P>
<P>
Technical renovation of the equipment since 1996 has resulted
in a saving of more than 300,000 tons of coal and 566 million
kilowatts-hour of electricity and a reduction of 155,000 tons of
pollutants.
</P>
<P>
Official figures also show that technical advances have enabled
Shandong to reduce the discharge of 120 million tons of solid
industrial wastes for five years between 1991 and 1995.
</P>
<P>
Because of the development of environmental protection
technology, the Dezhou Heat and Power Plant, for example, is now
able to re-use the 100,000 tons of powder coal it discharges each
year, generating some 112 million yuan in gross profits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
