<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Dollar Makes Dramatic Comeback </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean Dollar has made a
dramatic comeback, strengthening against major international
currencies, the daily Herald newspaper Thursday quoted foreign
currency analysts as reporting.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean Dollar's recovery ensued from the on-going
visit to the country by an International Money Fund (IMF) team,
reduced import demand and inflow of export earnings, mainly from
tobacco, said the report.
</P>
<P>
At the close of foreign currency trading Wednesday, some banks
were buying U.S. Dollars for 19 Zimbabwean Dollars and selling
them for 24 Zimbabwean Dollars, narrowing down the spreads
compared to the tradings on Monday and Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, banks were buying the U.S. Dollars for 22
Zimbabwean Dollars and selling them for 28 Zimbabwean Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Optimism shown by the visiting IMF team saw the market
returning to a bit of normalcy, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign currency analysts and dealers said that the market was
somehow correcting itself and confidence was slowly returning,
the report added.  
