<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Companies Invest More in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's investment in
Zhangzhou, a coastal city of east China's Fujian Province,
continued to grow in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Zhangzhou approved 112 Hong Kong-funded enterprises in the
first six months, about 54 percent of the number of all
overseas-funded firms were established during the period. Hong
Kong companies' pledged investment of 240 million U.S. dollars was
57 percent of the total contracted investment in Zhangzhou for the
January-June period.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, the number of Hong Kong-funded enterprises
and the value of contracted investment was up 111 percent and 37
percent, respectively, from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed the surge in investment from Hong
Kong to strengthening economic and trade contacts between
Zhangzhou and Hong Kong, the introduction of a series of
preferential policies for investors, and the increased effort to
improve the local investment environment. 
