<HEADLINE> Anhui Province to Renovate Rural Power Grid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
become the first in China to launch a campaign to renovate its
rural power grid.
</P>
<P>
The effort is part of a national drive to spur economic growth
through the renovation of the power grid in the vast rural
areas. Nationwide, 100 billion yuan has been planned for the
renovation endeavor.
</P>
<P>
In the next two to three years, Anhui will renovate more than
30,000 kilometers (km) of 10-kilovolt electric wire, more than
30,000 power transmitters, and 130,000 km of low-voltage wire. The
total renovation cost has been budgeted at 3.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
As the first step, the power-supplying facilities across the
province's 70 counties will be renovated within this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
