<HEADLINE> Rainfall Along Yangtze Continues to Cause Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Rainfall along the Yangtze River
Valley in central and east China is expected to continue until
Sunday, which means at least
half a month for the river's water level to drop below the danger
mark, experts said.
</P>
<P>
The prevailing No.2 tropical storm will certainly worsen the
already serious flood situation, especially in Jiangxi and Hubei
provinces, sources from the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters told Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
Drizzle or moderate rainfall is expected in some central,
southwest, and east China provinces, while parts of Hubei, the
Hanshui River Valley, and central parts of Jiangxi should receive
heavy or torrential rain in the next two days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
