<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall for Fourth Day in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed lowest in the
fourth consecutive trading day in Tokyo Thursday as banking shares
resumed their downward spiral.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange dropped 115.94 points, or 0.72
percent from Wednesday's close to end at 15,876.22, the lowest
level in nearly six weeks.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, lost 8.69 points or 0.70 percent to 1,227.09.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section went slightly up to an estimated
380 million shares from Wednesday's 363.68 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,335 issues listed on the First Section, decliners
exceeded gainers 689 to 432, with 165 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the Japanese government submitted to the Diet
(parliament) its "bridge bank" bill to take over failed banks, but
critics say the plan is appropriate for smaller- to medium-sized
financial institutions, not the country's biggest lenders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
