<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 08:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran to Reduce Diplomatic Missions Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Iran has decided to close a number
of diplomatic missions abroad in line with the government's
austerity plan, the Tehran Times daily reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The plan to reduce the number of Iranian diplomatic missions
and their staff would be given top priority to help the government
slash spendings, Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi said
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi did not specify the countries where the Iranian
embassies will be closed.
</P>
<P>
But he said that "we are going to close our diplomatic missions
in countries which do not have very friendly relations with Iran
and those which do not have significant economic cooperation with
our country."
</P>
<P>
This decision was in line with an economic plan announced by
President Mohammad Khatami last Sunday, which was aimed at
lowering the financial burden of the government and helping revive
the oil-dependent economy.
</P>
<P>
Khatami said the government is facing mounting pressures due to
the decrease in foreign exchange revenues as a result of oil price
fall in the world market in the past year.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Ministry has worked out a program to train
diplomats in how to promote trade with foreign countries where
they are assigned to work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980806.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Foreign Branch Bank Opens in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Nova Scotia in
Canada opened a branch bank in Chongqing in southwest China this
week.
</P>
<P>
This was the first foreign bank approved to open a branch in
Chongqing since the city was upgraded to the status of China's
fourth centrally-administered municipality in March of 1997.
</P>
<P>
It has adopted a series of preferential measures to attract
investment from abroad. To date, the Sumitomo Bank of Japan and
Hong Kong-based Po Sang Bank Ltd. and the Bank of East Asia have
opened representative offices in Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
Nova Scotia Bank has 1,600 branch banks and representative
offices in more than 50 counties. It has opened banks in Guangzhou
and Chongqing and a representative office in Beijing since the
first one was inaugurated in 1982. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
