<DOCNO> XIE19980806.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Claim Over 2,000 Lives In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Seasonal floods, since June, have
claimed more than 2,000 lives, Vice-Minister of Water Resources
Zhou Wenzhi announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhou told a news conference that 90 percent of the deaths were
caused by flood waters, landslides and mud-flows, and the rest
were killed by capsizings, electrocutions and road accidents.
</P>
<P>
However, no one was killed when some 13 million people who had
been affected were relocated on large-scale, he noted.
</P>
<P>
A number of productive dykes of the Yangtze River have
collapsed because of sustained high water levels, huge water flows
and weakness in some dykes, according to Zhao Chunming, deputy
director of the Office of the State Flood Control and Drought
Relief Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
On August 1, productive dykes in Jiayu County, Hubei Province,
collapsed, which led a loss of 13 lives including five
soldiers. All the 50,000 local residents were removed to safe
places, Zhao said at the same news conference.
</P>
<P>
In another case, no one were killed when dykes around a small
island in the Yangtze River went breached on August 4. All the
40,000 villagers were relocated in time, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhao stressed that so far all major Yangtze dykes, major cities
and key roads and railways have remained intact.
</P>
<P>
The floods have brought enormous economic losses to flood-hit
areas, said Vice-Minister of Civil Affairs Fan Baojun, noting that
240 million people in 28 provinces, municipalities and autonomous
regions have been affected by the floods, with 13.8 million people
relocated to safe places, 5.58 million houses destroyed, and 12.05
million houses suffering damages.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 21.53 million ha. of farmland were affected,
including 4.78 million ha. of farmlands with their crops totally
destroyed, according to the vice-minister.
</P>
<P>
The central government has provided more than 1.9 billion yuan
worth of relief funds and large quantities of relief materials to
the flood-affected areas, and local governments in 12 provinces
and municipalities have also appropriated 720 million yuan for the
same purpose.
</P>
<P>
The local governments have distributed nearly 290,000 tons of
cereals and 6.31 million pieces of wears and quilts to flood
victims, while 346,000 make-shifts have been erected for those who
have been made homeless by the floods, said the official.
</P>
<P>
Fan pledged that each of the flood victims will receive a half
kg of grain every day.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have also aroused people to make donations to
the flood victims. So far, Hunan and Hubei, the two most affected
provinces, have got 47 million yuan in cash and 41.8 million yuan
in kind, he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-minister paid tribute to the army, police and reserve
servicemen for the remarkable role they have played in battling
against the floods. Meanwhile, he noted, the troops and policemen
have also made large amount of donations.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the government will work hard to implement the
rehabilitation programs and build winter-shelters for the
homeless, and flood victims will get their winter clothing and
quilts from the government and donors, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also assured that all donations will be properly used as
efforts will be made to step up supervision and management over
the distribution of donations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
