<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Eritrea Soccer Teams to Meet in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian National Team
will meet the Eritrean side on August 23 in Cairo, Egypt, in the
African Cup of Nations preliminary, a report said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Originally the first leg Ethio-Eritrea match was scheduled to
take place in Addis Ababa on August 2, but postponed by the
Confederation of African Football (CAF) because of the
prevailing border tension between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the African football governing body, CAF, Ethiopia
and Eritrea will play a single match as opposed to the traditional
home and away matches and the winner will advance to the group
qualification series along with Ghana and Cameroon which are due
to begin in September.
</P>
<P>
The Cairo match will be the first time for the two national
teams to face each other in an international competition.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
