<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 08:00 GMT, August 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles -- Soybean futures Wednesday fell close to
four-year lows on the Chicago Board of Trade, weighed down by
expectations for large supplies and weak demand, reports said
today.
</P>
<P>
Soybeans for November delivery, representing prices after the
fall harvest, fell 6.5 cents to 5.4125 U.S. dollar a bushel, the
lowest since October 1994. (BC-US-Soybean-Futures)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian authorities decided Tuesday to invest heavily
in building new ports and renovating outdated ones to improve the
handling capacity of ships, the Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a joint meeting between the Ministry
of Transport and the Ministry of Railroads.
</P>
<P>
The two ministries will first speed up the renovation of ports
in St. Petersburg and Novorossiysk as well as building three new
ports along the Gulf of Finland, a senior official
said. (BC-Russia-Port)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WARSAW -- The Polish economy grew by 6.7 percent in the first
half of this year over the same period last year, but it has
started to show signs of a slowdown amid worries over increasing
trade deficit and inflation. (BC-Poland-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ZAGREB -- Croatian police, in a joint operation with their
Slovenian counterparts, seized 38 kilograms of heroin and cut off
a drug-trafficking route from Bosnia to West Europe, a Croatian
Interior Ministry official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seized drug has a market value of 3.3 million U.S. dollars,
the official told a press conference. (BC-Croatia-Slovania-Drugs)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic Wednesday
appealed to ethnic Kosovo Albanians to return home, and described
the regularization of life there as an urgent task.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia's Tanjug news agency quoted Milosovic as saying that
while drawing a clear distinction between Kosovo's Albanian
civilians and terrorists, the Yugoslavian government would take
proper measures to ensure the refugees' safety and security of
property. (BC-Yugoslavia-Milosevic-Ethnic Albanians)
</P>
