<HEADLINE> Bayer Set up Two Joint Ventures in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, Augest 6 (Xinhua) -- Bayer, the German-based chemical
and health care group, is to establish two joint ventures in east
China's Shanghai City to make agrochemicals and household
insecticides.
</P>
<P>
A total of 80 million Deutsche Mark (DM) (45 million
U.S. dollars) will be invested in the two projects.
</P>
<P>
Bayer signed contracts with its partner company Shanghai
Zhongxi Pharmaceuticals Co. today in Shanghai. Under the
agreement, Bayer will hold a stake of 70 percent in each of the
two joint ventures, while the Chinese company hold the remaining
30 percent in each.
</P>
<P>
Production facilities are to be built up at an integrated site
in the Xinghuo Special Economic Development Zone in Pudong
District in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Under the name of Bayer Zhongxi Agrochemical Co., Bayer will
manufacture pyrethroid-based agrochemicals such as Baythroid and
Bulldock and the Bayer Zhongxi Consumer Care Co. will produce the
well-known range of Baygon insecticides.
</P>
<P>
The new ventures are expected to expand Bayer's business in
China and strengthen Bayer's position in the Chinese life sciences
market, a manager of Bayer said.
</P>
<P>
Bayer has 12 joint ventures in China, of which seven have already
start production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
