<HEADLINE> China Striving to Reduce Flood Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The joint efforts of Chinese
people from all walks of life have ensured the safety of major
rivers and lakes and leading cities and railways, ruducing the
losses to the minimum level, according to a senior flood control
official.
</P>
<P>
Since the outbreak of floods in many parts of China,
governments at all levels have made flood control the focal point
of their work, Zhou Wenzhi, secretary-general of the State Flood
Control and Drought Relief Headquarters, told a press conference
here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"Thanks to the close cooperation of various departments and the
concerted efforts of soldiers and the general public, the safety
of the embankments of major rivers and lakes and leading cities
and railways have been guaranteed and the flood losses have been
reduced to the minimum," said Zhou, who is also vice-minister of
Water Resources. 
</P>
