<DOCNO> XIE19980806.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Strengthens Protection of Agricultural Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
has adopted a series of laws and regulations designed to protect
the agricultural environment.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the province has per capita arable land of only
0.5 mu (15 mu equal one hectare) has stymied agricultural
development, with rising pollution exacerbating the situation even
further.
</P>
<P>
The province has responded by enacting environmental protection
regulations which require governments at all levels to include the
protection of agricultural environment in local economic and social
development programs.
</P>
<P>
The regulation upholds the principle of "putting prevention
first and combining prevention with pollution control" in
protecting the agricultural environment. It also contains
stipulations related to the establishment of a responsibility
system for strengthening environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The regulation prohibits the construction or expansion of
environmentally unsound projects; strictly prohibits discharges of
industrial wastewater, gases and dust particles into the
agricultural environment; and bans discharges of garbage and solid
waste materials into rivers and lakes.
</P>
<P>
The regulation, which will take effect on October 1, outlines
strict penalties for polluters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
