<HEADLINE> International Congress of Genetics to Open in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The 18th International Congress
of Genetics (ICG) will be held at the Beijing International
Convention Center Aug. 10-15. Preparatory work for the conference
has been in full swing, according to a congress organizer.
</P>
<P>
About 1,600 geneticists from 53 countries -- including the
United States, Britain, Germany, Japan, India, Russia and China --
have applied for attendance, said Chen Siliang, an official with
the ICG Chinese organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
A dozen keynote lectures and 55 symposiums will be held during
the six-day event. About 150 leading geneticists are scheduled to
give speeches, discussing the latest findings in genetics which
can be used to increase grain production, treat diseases and
protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the 18th ICG, "Genetics -- A Better Life for All,"
underlines the purpose of the congress, which is the application
of genetic research findings to the improvement of the quality of
human life.
</P>
<P>
Some subjects -- such as the human genome project, cloning
technology and the prevention of abuse of genetic technology --
are expected to be controversial during the academic event, which
is held every five years.
</P>
<P>
"China for the first time hosts such a big congress of
genetics; it will be a good opportunity for Chinese geneticists to
conduct exchanges," said Prof. Zhu Lihuang, deputy director of the
Institute of Genetics under the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The International Genetics Federation plans to elect a new
executive board during the congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
