<HEADLINE> Russia to Invest in Ports to Raise Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian authorities decided
Tuesday to invest heavily in building new ports and renovating
outdated ones to improve the handling capacity of ships, the
Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a joint meeting between the Ministry
of Transport and the Ministry of Railroads.
</P>
<P>
The two ministries will first speed up the renovation of ports
in St. Petersburg and Novorossiysk as well as building three new
ports along the Gulf of Finland, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
Along with the construction of facilities such as railways
leading to the ports, the projects will cost above one billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Due to the poor capacity of its own ports, Russia in recent
years has had to seek help from ports in neighboring countries to
handle goods. 
</P>
