<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Andrea Stinson and Vicky
Bullett combined to score 36 points to help the Charlotte Sting
beat the New York Liberty 69-61 in the WNBA games on Wednesday
night.
</P>
<P>
Stinson had 19 points while Bullett added 17 plus nine reb
ounds.The Sting, with a record of 17-8 against New York's 14-10,
pushed its lead over the Liberty to 2 1/2 games in the Eastern
Conference with five games remaining. Charlotte leads
second-placed Cleveland by two games.
</P>
<P>
