73-61 in Auburn Hills. Korie Hlede scored nine points in a 16-2
second-half run and led the winning team with 20 points. Raija
Mujanovic added 15 and Sandy Brondello netted 12 for the
Sparks,which holds a 10-14 record.
</P>
<P>
