<DOCNO> XIE19980806.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Wheat Harvest Steady </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Despite a shrinking sowing area,
Heilongjiang, a leading grain producer in northeast China,
expects to harvest 3.2 billion kilograms of wheat this year,
roughly the same as last year's output.
</P>
<P>
The province has planted spring wheat on 960,000 hectares this
year, with an average per hectare yield of 3,315 kilograms, 8.4
percent higher than last year's output.
</P>
<P>
Over 95 percent of this wheat was planted under a unified
standard. New strains which are high-yielding, disease-resistant
and contain a high gluten content were sown on 666,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
So far, 40 percent of the wheat has been harvested, and local
grain departments have been urged to prepare for the purchase of
all the new wheat the farmers turn into the state. 
</P>
