<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Model Village (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhang, formerly director of the Hangmin Village Bleaching and
Dyeing Plant, disclosed that his group's employees are not only
local young and middle-aged villagers, but also include over 5,000
workers from other places to meet production demands.
</P>
<P>
What makes this one different from other villages in China is
that Hangmin villagers have no contracted farmland or private
plots, however they are not worried about their vegetable
baskets.
</P>
<P>
That's because 18 young and middle-aged villagers are
responsible for farming the village's 53 hectares of arable
land, and the production of non-staple foods for the whole village.
</P>
<P>
At present, village education has no tuition fees for
kindergarten through secondary school. Elderly people over the age
of 55 get a 60-yuan monthly pension, and retired workers receive
70 percent of their former salaries.
</P>
<P>
Village leaders have not forgotten to enrich the cultural lives
of the villagers, said Zhu Chongqing. Two years ago, the village
used 12 million yuan (1.45 million U.S. dollars) to build a
cultural center which includes ballrooms, a library, reading
rooms, a theater, and swimming pools. Villagers usually visit the
center in the evening.
</P>
<P>
These remarkable achievements have attracted attention at
home and abroad. Many people, including President Jiang Zemin, have
visited Hangmin Village.
</P>
<P>
Several years ago, a United Nations official visited the
village and said Hangmin could rival any developed village in the
world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980806.0261 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Growing Number Of Fishing Mishaps In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Safety has become a problem for
people in the fishing industry in China, government authorities
warn.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, there were 198 accidents at
sea, 201 fishing boats were involved in wrecks, and over 200
fishermen were hurt and about 9 million yuan (1 million
U.S. dollars) in losses totalled up.
</P>
<P>
Officials say the situation is getting worse because of a
neglect of safety procedures by both managers and fishermen, a
relaxation in law enforcement, and the low technical level of the
industry. The abnormal weather conditions this year are also being
blamed.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture's Fishery Department recently
issued a notice telling industry officials across the country to
increase safety awareness on fishing boats and to improve safety
inspections on fishing boats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
