<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Four were killed, 20 injured in two
powerful earthquakes in Ecuador on Tuesday, the civil defense
forces reported.
</P>
<P>
The earthquakes measured 5.7 and 7.1 on the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
The shakes were felt in most of the country, damaging more than
200 buildings around the the epicenter of Caraquez Bay, about 340
kilometers southwest of the capital.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, an Ecuadoran cargo plane began delivering
emergency food, water, medicine and tents to thousands of victims.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's quakes came as Ecuadorans are trying to recover from
El Nino-generated storms, floods and landslides that have left
thousands homeless along western coastal areas. 
