<HEADLINE> Shanghai Residents Buy More Apartments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Residents of this largest
economic and financial center in China purchase an average of 277
apartments each day, according to the municipal real estate trade
center.
</P>
<P>
Overall, Shanghai residents purchased 24,200 apartments in the
first half of this year, in addition to 26,400 flats sold in
advance. This combined figure is 71 percent more than in the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
As incomes rise and housing reform deepens, Shanghai residents
are becoming more willing and financially able to purchase their
own houses. More than half of Shanghai's commodity apartments have
been sold to individuals since 1994.
</P>
<P>
Since the start of this year, real estate developers have
intensified housing sales promotion while banks have repeatedly
lowered mortgage rates, resulting in growing housing
sales.
</P>
<P>
Individuals accounted for 89 percent of all residential
buyers in Shanghai in the first six months of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
