<HEADLINE> Sampaio Optimistic About Portugese-Chinese Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Portugese President Jorge Sampaio
said on Wednesday that he was optimistic about the future prospect
of Portugese-Chinese relations and the smooth transition of power
in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with outgoing Chinese Ambassador to Portugal Wei Dong,
Sampaio said the two countries, in addition to political ties,
should also promote cooperation in the economic sector.
</P>
<P>
He recalled his visit to China last year; he said his talks
with the Chinese leaders were "fruitful."
</P>
<P>
Portugese Prime Minister Antonio Gusterres also met the
outgoing Chinese ambassador the same day. Gusterres termed China
as a peace-loving country that has never invaded any other country.
</P>
<P>
The Portugese government attaches importance to developing
friendly relations with China and hopes to see a prosperous and
united China in the near future, he said. 
</P>
