<HEADLINE> Pakistani Arrested for Cockatoo Smuggling in Jakarta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A Pakistan International Airlines
flight attendant has been arrested by Soekarno-Hatta International
Airport officers here for attempting to smuggle two black
cockatoos to Karachi, the Jakarta Post reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani man was apprehended at the airport on Tuesday,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to airport quarantine chief Lukas A. Tonga, the two
cockatoos are worth between 1,500 and 2,000 U.S. dollars each on
black markets overseas.
</P>
<P>
The black cockatoo is a protected species in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Last Saturday, airport officers also foiled an attempt to
smuggle out 1,024 cobras, which are also protected animals under
Indonesian law. 
