<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Participate in Shanghai Tourism Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 6 (Xinhua)-- A delegation from the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) will, for the first time, take
part in the '98 Shanghai Tourism Festival scheduled for October 10
to November 8, a representative of Hong Kong Tourist Association
(HKTA) said here last week.
</P>
<P>
Scenery models designed by the HKTA will be placed on the
People's Square in front of the Shanghai municipal government
building during the festival to display major sightseeing spots in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
According to the representative, cooperation in tourism between
Shanghai and Hong Kong is being enhanced. Besides sightseeing
tours, the cooperation has now been extended to exhibitions,
conferences and other aspects, the representative said.
</P>
<P>
The HKTA has decided to set up an office in Shanghai next year,
the representative said, adding that it is the second office of
the HKTA on the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Hong Kong tourist arrivals in the Chinese mainland
reached 30 million, while visitors from the mainland to Hong Kong
totaled 2.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese mainland has now replaced Japan as the first
destination for Hong Kong's tourists.
</P>
<P>
The HKTA will also send a delegation to take part in the '98
China International Tourist Fair to be held during the festival,
which is expected to be attended by about 10,000 people from
international tourist circles. 
</P>
