<HEADLINE> Leading Property Insurer Fulfills 55 Percent of 1998 Income Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- People's Insurance (Property)
Co. of China Ltd (PICC Property), China's top property insurer,
announced on Wednesday that it earned 22.5 billion yuan (2.71
billion US dollars) in premium income in the first half of this
year.
</P>
<P>
According to today's China Daily, the income, seven percent
higher than that of the year-ago period, represents 55 percent of
the company's goal for 1998.
</P>
<P>
During the first six months, the company paid 9 billion yuan
(1.08 billion US dollars) in compensation, 1.1 billion yuan (132
million US dollars) more than in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Company officials confirmed a confidence of meeting this year's
target of 40 billion yuan (4.8 billion US dollars) in premium
income despite the severe natural mishaps.
</P>
<P>
The company has recorded a loss of insured properties worth
2.65 billion yuan (319.2 million US dollars) in flood-ravaged
areas, including Jiangxi, Guangdong, Anhui, Zhejiang and Sichuan
provinces, since mid-June.
</P>
<P>
While, employees of PICC Property's local branches have helped
to rescue insured properties worth 4.5 billion yuan (542 million
US dollars) from flooded areas.
</P>
<P>
Sun Xiyue, general manager of PICC Property, said that the
company will try to maintain the income momentum by making some
policy adjustment. And revised policies for employer
responsibility insurance, family property insurance and housing
loan insurance will become available in the second half of the
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
