<HEADLINE> Tibet Gets Meteorology Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Meteorological departments from
across China have provided huge financial, technical and
human resources to help improve the meteorological services in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
A meeting on meteorology aid for Tibet held here recently was
informed that between 1994 and 1997 the China Meteorological
Bureau earmarked more than 82.4 million yuan (some 10 million
U.S. dollars) for the meteorological development in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the bureau allocated a special fund of more than 1.3
million yuan to help the autonomous region set up a research
institute on air quality in the region.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, the bureau has sent 21 officials to Tibet for
technical assistance.
</P>
<P>
Meteorological departments from all over the country have
injected more than 3.2 million yuan to aid more than 80
meteorological projects in the region. 
</P>
