<HEADLINE> Life Expectancy in Colombia Reaches 71 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The average life
expectancy for Colombians will be 71.68 years of age from 1998 to
2000, according to data released Wednesday by the National
Statistics Administrative Department (DANE).
</P>
<P>
The data show that men's life expectancy will be 68.6, while
women 74.91.
</P>
<P>
The DANE attributed the age gap between men and women to
military violence and social conflict, which affects more men than
women.
</P>
<P>
Based on the 1993 census, the DANE forecast is that Colombia's
population will reach 40.826 million in 1998, 20.177 million will
be men, 20.485 million will be women.
</P>
<P>
During 1991-1995, many men died as the result of violence at
the ages ranging from 15 to 44 years, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
