<HEADLINE> Seven Killed in Berlin House Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A total of seven bodies have been
recovered from the rubble of a collapsed apartment house in Berlin
until Wednesday evening after a suspected gas explosion destroyed
the house early Tuesday morning, German rescue workers said.
</P>
<P>
The seven dead were all those who were reported missing after
the four-storey apartment house in a western district of Berlin
collapsed at about 6:00 a.m. Tuesday after a huge explosion,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The victims included a 13-year-old boy whose parents have
survived the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of rescue workers, helped by specially trained dogs
and high-tech detecting devices, have been working round the clock
to remove the rubble by hand in a bid to search for possible
survivors.
</P>
<P>
Of the 21 registered tenants of the apartment house, some dug
themselves out of the debris and several others were found not in
the house when the accident occurred.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that rescue workers would continue to clear up
the rubble until Thursday in order to make sure there were no
unexpected victims.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said that the explosion might have been triggered
by a gas leak in the basement of the building, but the exact cause
could only be made clear in days or weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
