<HEADLINE> EU OKs Interactive Service Joint Venture in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission
announced on Wednesday its approval of a joint venture of
interactive services to non-enterprise customers in France.
</P>
<P>
The commission, the executive body of the 15-nation European
Union, made the approval on the finding that the joint operation
will neither create or strengthen a dominant position nor will it
lead to anti-competitive cooperation between the parent companies.
</P>
<P>
The full-function joint venture, to be known as AOL/CIS France,
will be formed among Cegetel, Canal Plus, America Online and
Bertelsmann.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will have a combined share of between 32
percent and 37 percent on the dial-up Internet access market in
France while France Telecom, the current leader in the country,
still has a significant market share.
</P>
<P>
The commission made its appraisal of the joint venture in
accordance with the European Community Treaty.  
</P>
