parliament voted to freeze U.N. weapons inspections.
</P>
<P>
Iraq's national Assembly, meeting after chief U.N. weapons
inspector Richard Butler cut short a visit to Baghdad on Tuesday,
voted unanimously to suspend U.N. weapons inspections. The move
has yet to be endorsed by Iraqs President Saddam Hussein.
</P>
