opposition parties called it a fraud.
</P>
<P>
They are calling on King Letsie III to intervene, following
disclosures, based on an audit of the May election results, that
the results were rigged in favor of the LCD.
</P>
<P>
The protesters have vowed to continue with their action until
the monarchy steps in.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrations turned violent Wednesday when police used
rubber bullets and water canyon to disperse protesters, according
to South Africa's national television, the SABC.
</P>
<P>
Police had to close the gates of the National Assembly to stop
the crowd from entering.
</P>
<P>
Mosisili was taken hostage for an hour after he made his
speech in parliament, said SABC.
</P>
<P>
Mosisili is expected to meet the king later Wednesday, for
what government officials have called "regular Wednesday
briefings."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Lesotho government said Wednesday that it would
leave enforcement of the law and control of the demonstrations to
the police, but stressed it would not allow the situation to
threaten the country's peace and stability. 
</P>
