<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Garda (police) Representative
Association (GRA) in Ireland, representing three quarters of the
country's 10,900-strong police force, Wednesday voted to accept a
government offer of a nine percent wage increase.
</P>
<P>
