<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Gold Producer Lists on N.Y. Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The world's largest gold
producer, Anglogold, Wednesday became the first South African
company to list on the New York Stock Exchange, local media
reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking via a video conference from New York, Anglogold chief
executive Bobby Godsell said the listing was an important step in
developing a globally competitive, investor friendly company.
</P>
<P>
Anglogold is also listed on stock markets in Johannesburg,
London, Paris and Brussels.
</P>
<P>
With an annual production of seven million ounces and reserves
of 140 million ounces, the company has a market capitalization of
four billion U.S. Dollars. It has operations in South Africa,
Mali and Namibia, and a 50-million-Dollar African exploration
program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
